10/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- VMRO-DPMNE, the main opposition party, will return to parliament after a two-month boycott, deputy leader Marjan Gjorcev announced Thursday (9 January). Its first session will be on 23 January, he said, adding that the return would be positive not only for the party but for the democratic process.
Meanwhile, the daily <I> Dnevnik</I> reports Friday that the Macedonian Army will include 2400 officers and non-commissioned officers of ethnic Albanian origin by 2005, in accordance with the Ohrid peace accords. (Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 10/01/03; A1 TV, MIA - 09/01/03)
